                            <container4_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T12:29:26.899-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Other key features of the school include:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>A 3,300-square-foot cafeteria with floor-to-ceiling windows&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Hot meal service, which wasn’t available at the former school&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>A collegiate style gathering place known as the “Learning Stairs” where students, teachers and staff can meet for announcements and informal events&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>A new music room, fitness center and 1,800-square-foot media center&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Six new science labs and new maker spaces, enabling teachers to expand academic curricula&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Private spaces where students can meet with occupational therapists, social workers and nurses, keeping social-emotional learning and physical health in mind&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>The district’s first, custom-built sensory room – a therapeutic space which includes both calming and active sides to support students’ well-being&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“The new Neal Math and Science Academy provides a modernized learning environment that reflects the potential of North Chicago students and AbbVie’s culture of giving back to our communities,” said Laura Schumacher, vice chairman, external affairs and chief legal officer, AbbVie.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T12:29:05.341-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T12:29:05.341-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1661545829678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T12:10:17.022-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T12:29:41.010-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="The public-private partnership that propelled the project"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T12:41:04.037-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>AbbVie and the North Chicago School District selected&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://iff.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>IFF&lt;/a>, a mission-driven lender, real estate consultant and developer, to facilitate this project. The school was also built with input from the district; staff; and two North Chicago community advisory groups, comprised of students, teachers, parents, school and district staff members, representatives from the Naval Station Great Lakes (where many parents of students are stationed), and advisors from the City of North Chicago.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>One objective partners shared was a desire to make the construction of the school an economic catalyst for North Chicago, a city that’s home to approximately 30,000 residents, 20% of whom live below the poverty line, according to the 2020 census. To achieve this goal, IFF prioritized hiring local minority, women and veteran tradesman and subcontractors. By integrating community voices and expertise, this project demonstrated the potential public-private partnerships have in driving equitable community development.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“By integrating community and student voices at each stage of the process and setting ambitious goals to hire locally and keep dollars in the community, we’ve ensured that AbbVie’s $40 million investment will lead to the greatest possible impact for North Chicago,” says Jenny Boyts, director of school services, IFF.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T12:29:05.341-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T12:29:05.341-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1661545829678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T12:10:17.022-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T13:18:33.131-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="AbbVie’s legacy of supporting student success in North Chicago"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h5"/>
                                <text2_copy_325261949
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T12:40:21.533-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>AbbVie’s support for the project builds on its long-running relationship with the city of North Chicago, which is home to the company’s headquarters. Since 2013, AbbVie has maintained a partnership with the North Chicago School District to improve student success across the district. Throughout those years employees have committed upwards of 100,000 volunteer hours in the community.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>As volunteers, employees have renovated libraries and built learning resource centers, maker spaces and new career pathways facilities, which has resulted in significant increases in student engagement in literacy and STEM subjects. As part of AbbVie’s annual global volunteer event, known as Week of Possibilities, employees also took part in clearing out desks and furniture from the old Neal. Additionally, the AbbVie Foundation has made significant investments in Teach for America, North Chicago Community Partners and Innovations for Learning, which support students in North Chicago through a variety of programs.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We at AbbVie could not be prouder to support the creation of this new school which will help the young people in our community grow, learn and reach their full potential,” Schumacher concludes.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <text
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-06T13:18:57.054-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-06T13:19:24.440-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>Media inquires:&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Name: Frank Benenati&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Email:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:frank.benenati@abbvie.com&quot;>frank.benenati@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
